<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Holly Willoughby was left in hysterics on Wednesday's episode of This Morning during a gender reveal party for a penguin.</p>

<p>The TV presenter, 39, could hardly contain herself as she and co-host Phillip Schofield spoke to Dr Scott Miller about the gender reveal at a zoo for the penguin, a female who was named Squirt because she kept 'popping'. </p>

<p>Speaking from the zoo via link, Dr Scott said: 'Is it possible to tell a male from a female? Normally as a vet, we would just turn an animal upside down and check for suitable plumbing.'</p>

<p>Fun: Holly Willoughby was left in hysterics on Wednesday's episode of This Morning during a gender reveal party for a penguin</p>

<p>Phillip then turned to Holly and said: 'Even if it was a giraffe?' prompting her to burst into a fit of giggles. </p>

<p>Afterwards, Phillip said: 'That was a bizarre way to start the show.'</p>

<p>Holly replied: 'That's what I like to be talking about actually.'</p>

<p>'Penguins?' Phillip said. </p>

<p>Party: Holly could hardly contain herself as she and Phillip Schofield spoke to Dr Scott Miller about the gender reveal at a zoo for the penguin, a female who was named Squirt because she kept 'popping'</p>

<p>Interesting segment: Afterwards, Phillip said: 'That was a bizarre way to start the show'</p>

<p>She answered: 'I mean, not just specifically penguins but nice stories.'</p>

<p>Phillip joked: 'I mean, over the next six months it's going to be quite hard to find a story a day about penguins but we'll give it a go!'</p>

<p>Laughing, Holly replied: 'That's a challenge for you!</p>

<p>Speaking to the viewers, Phillip said: 'I have to say I don't know if it's just the point today we've just been pushed over the edge. We can't take any more. There's an element of hysteria!' </p>

<p>Phillip joked: 'I mean, over the next six months it's going to be quite hard to find a story a day about penguins but we'll give it a go!'</p>

<p>Still laughing, Holly said: 'Honestly, I don't know what's happened to me! I think it is that! </p>

<p>'Everything feels so much to deal with in your own head, I can't stop laughing!'</p>

<p>'It's a coping mechanism,' Phillip told her. </p>

<p>This Morning airs Monday to Friday on ITV at 10am. </p>

